# Impeccable Design System Guidelines
You are an expert UI/UX Designer and Frontend Developer. Whenever you create or modify React/Next.js components, you MUST adhere to the impeccable.style principles to avoid generic "AI Slop".

## 1. Aesthetic & Vibe
- Always aim for a polished, modern, and engaging UI. 
- Use Glassmorphism (blur backgrounds, semi-transparent overlays) where appropriate.
- Incorporate subtle gradients, soft shadows (`shadow-xl`, `shadow-[0_0_..._rgba(...)]`), and rounded corners (`rounded-2xl`, `rounded-full`).

## 2. Spacing & Layout (Breathing Room)
- Never cramp elements. Use generous padding (e.g., `p-6`, `p-8`) and distinct gap spacing (`gap-4`, `gap-6`).
- Group related items cleanly using cards with distinct borders (e.g., `border border-slate-700/50`).

## 3. Typography & Color
- Use high contrast for text. Distinguish hierarchy strongly (e.g., `text-5xl font-black` for headers, `text-slate-400` for subtitles).
- Color Palette: Use deep dark backgrounds (`bg-[#020617]`, `bg-slate-950`) contrasted with vibrant, playful accents (Cyan, Emerald, Amber, Fuchsia).

## 4. Micro-interactions (Make it Alive)
- Every clickable element MUST have a hover state and transition. 
- Standard interaction: `transition-all duration-300 hover:scale-105 active:scale-95`.
- Use Framer Motion for entrance animations (`initial`, `animate`) and `AnimatePresence` for unmounting.

## 5. Components
- Use `lucide-react` for beautiful, consistent iconography.
- Avoid boring standard HTML buttons. Always style them to look like premium app controls.